        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You have been specially trained to use guile and magic to reveal hidden threats. You must select @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Vindicator Dedication] as your 2nd-level class feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> You must be a ranger.</p>\n<p><strong>Vindicator Adjustments:</strong> You must choose a deity to be a follower of, and you gain your deity's sanctification.</p>\n<p>You are trained in Religion instead of Nature.</p>\n<p>You are trained in your deity's favored weapon. If your deity's favored weapon is a simple weapon or unarmed attack with a damage die smaller than d6, you gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Deadly Simplicity] feat. If your deity's favored weapon is an advanced weapon, your proficiency with it is equal to your proficiency with martial weapons.</p>\n<p>You must choose the vindication edge for your hunter's edge.</p>\n<p>You learn warden spells as divine spells instead of primal spells, and your spellcasting attribute is Wisdom. When you gain domain spells via the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Domain Initiate] or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Advanced Domain] feats, they are warden spells for the purposes of all your vindicator feats and abilities.</p><h2>Vindication Edge</h2><p>Your specialized training gives you a unique edge that allows you to more effectively bring the tools of your faith to bear against the monsters that lurk in the night or hide among the faithful.</p>\n<p>You gain a +1 status bonus to your spell attack rolls against your hunted prey, and they take a –1 status penalty to their saving throws against divine spells you cast. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Vindicator's Mark] warden spell.</p><h2>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.classfeatures.Item.Trackless Journey]{Trackless Journey }<span style=\"float:right\">5th</span></h2><p>Vindicators can choose to gain the benefits of this class feature in either urban or natural terrain, chosen at the time the class feature is gained.</p><h2>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.classfeatures.Item.Masterful Hunter] <span style=\"float:right\">17th</span></h2><p>The masterful hunter class feature gives an additional benefit based on your hunter's edge. Included here is the additional benefit for the vindication edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Vindication:</strong> You combine skill and magic to swiftly defeat your prey. The status bonus to divine spell attack rolls against your hunted prey increases to +2, and the status penalty to their saving throws against divine spells you cast is –2.</p>"
        },
